query: Analyze quantum computing error rates evolution from 2020 to 2025. Context: Track technological progress in quantum error correction. Goal: Identify specific error rate improvements, key milestones, and breakthrough moments with exact metrics and dates. Focus areas: 1) Year-by-year error rate metrics for superconducting qubits, 2) Ion trap systems, 3) Photonic approaches, 4) Error correction code implementations, 5) Breakthrough announcements from IBM, Google, IonQ, Rigetti. Success criteria: Exact error rate percentages/values, specific dates, peer-reviewed sources or official vendor announcements, quantitative improvements between years.
